	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 11:54 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi folks...<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; Just started a new bard on Drinal. She is level 5, and a heck of a lot of fun.<br>   Having gotten Selo's, and quested for my Hand Drum, once I hit level 5 I figured it would be wise to start drumming and running around to build up my drumming skill. But I can't hold my drum in my off hand. Why is this? It lists itself as only a secondary item. My best guess is that it counts as a weapon, and I therefore cannot put it in my off hand until 17 or whenever it is I get dual wield. Is this correct? If so, when should I start drumming? Should I wait until then? It hardly seems I can afford to put down my weapon at this point.<br><br>Thanks in advance!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>--<br>Dave, speaking for ZsaZsa<br>ZsaZsa Vavoom of Drinal<br>56th Level Paladin<br><br></td></tr>
